criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. Other types of avascular necrosis of the femoral head;
2. Required the application of hormone or immunosuppressant;
3. After hip surgery;
4. Diabetes, hyperthyroidism and other metabolic diseases;
5. Infection;
6. Combined immunodeficiency disease;
7. Tumor;
8. Very few high expectations, or not practical for patients.
